=2E=C2=A0
Selling electricity in a deregulated market is a low-margin, high-risk busi=
ness. It=E2=80=99s low margin because it=E2=80=99s competitive, and REPs ha=
ve to buy from generators and sell to price-sensitive consumers. It=E2=80=
=99s high risk because prices can fluctuate wildly. For most REPs, that mak=
