 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">As the demand for electricity is expected to double or trip=
le by 2050, solving the demand volatility is crucial. If you want to really=
 solve the grid bottleneck, you need residential batteries.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">So why is the vast majority of the battery installation grid-sc=
ale (i.e. next to the solar farm in our toy example)? A lot of financial an=
d operational reasons, it turns out.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">For one thi=
ng, batteries are expensive. Customers understandably don&#8217;t want to p=
ony up $15,000 for something that pays itself back in 12 years even after t=
he 30% IRA tax credit.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Private equity-back=
ed battery farms like </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/5cd44=
83a-efb9-4ce1-ad9b-f0b9c48fe020?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjm=
lXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decorati=
on: underline;">Broad Reach</a><span> (Apollo), </span><a href=3D"https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/897be69d-8895-425c-83e7-5b50172164a7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Jupiter</a><span> (BlackRock), an=
d </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/8a091863-022b-4564-9b41-0=
2304e9e7bff?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">aypa=
</a><span> (Blackstone) on the other hand, are happy underwriting that inve=
stment, signing offtake agreements to sell their power, and levering the he=
ll out of it at 70-80% loan-to-value to generate high levered returns.&#160=
;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">For another, acquiring individual residential=
 customers is expensive compared to just putting a bunch of batteries on on=
e piece of land.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">For a third, battery capacity i=
s wasted on individual homes. Customers can&#8217;t arbitrage price volatil=
ity in the way a professional battery farm operator can, which means that e=
ach kW of capacity is more valuable to battery farms than it is to individu=
al customers.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The list goes on. I know I&#8217;m=
 throwing a lot at you for an introduction, but to understand what Base is =
building and why, you need to grok how multifaceted the challenge is.&#160;=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To deploy batteries and fix the grid, Base can&=
#8217;t just build a battery; it needs to build a vertically integrated pow=
er </span><strong>company</strong><span> around batteries.&#160;</span></p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">The power company needs to excel at a whole lot of things=
: manufacturing, finance, distributed systems, power trading, customer acqu=
isition, consumer software, regulatory, and installation, to start. It need=
s to become a Retail Electric Provider (REP) itself.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">Technologies are tools. The better the tools builders have, the bigger=
 challenges they can solve. The focus should be on the challenge, not the t=
ool. The job of the entrepreneur tackling big, physical industries is to as=
semble whichever combination of tools, and whichever team of people who can=
 best wield them, is needed to do the job.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span=
>Base is one of the clearest examples of that approach that I&#8217;ve seen=
=2E It&#8217;s building a textbook </s=
pan><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/32b5d92c-ce04-4285-ace8-570a71e77053?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); te=
xt-decoration: underline;">Techno-Industrial</a><span>, vertically integrat=
ing a number of modern tools to make a big, old market cheaper and better. =
It&#8217;s built a team from SpaceX, Anduril, Blackstone, and Apple, where =
they honed their particular crafts. And it&#8217;s a case study in Techno-I=
ndustrial </span><em>strategy</em><span>: how do you fit all the tools toge=
ther to solve the one or two key problems that really matter?&#160;&#160;&#=
160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To that end, </span><a href=3D"https=
://substack.com/redirect/dfe0b3c3-6a07-4f82-8f93-13b29f6d3062?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: =
rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Zach Dell</a><span>, Justin&#=
8217;s co-founder, shared a series of memos the team has written from idea =
conception to Series A as he and the team started with an insight and explo=
red the best way to turn it into a business.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">&#8220;The grid is the bottleneck and batteries can unblock it&#8221; i=
s a big insight, but it&#8217;s just a starting point.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">Base is young, less than a year old. It&#8217;s well-capitalized, ha=
ving raised over $60 million from investors including Thrive Capital, Altim=
eter Capital, and Valor Equity Partners. Antonio Gracias, who has served on=
 the boards of Tesla and SpaceX, sits on Base&#8217;s board. Its team is st=
acked and its strategy is sound.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But because all=
 of Base&#8217;s accomplishments lay in the future, it&#8217;s a perfect op=
portunity to analyze its strategy with a clean sheet of paper and without t=
he benefit of hindsight. Given ideal starting conditions and a clear strate=
gy, can a startup come to compete with monopoly utilities and fix what may =
be the largest and most complex machine in the world, the grid?&#160;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Only time will tell. For today, we&#8217;re going to =
walk through the idea maze together to understand </span><strong>why</stron=
g><span> Base is building </span><strong>what</strong><span> it is, </span>=
<strong>how</strong><span>, </span><strong>where</strong><span>, and what i=
t means if they pull it off.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But we=
 have to start with </span><strong>who</strong><span>.&#160;&#160;</span></=
p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-appearance: optimiz=
elegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-appearance: opti=
mizelegibility; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; appearance: optimizele=
gibility; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-sys=
tem-headline, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Rob=
oto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', '=
Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16e=
m; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>Assembling a Based=
 Team</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Of the many insights that led to Base,=
 perhaps the most important was the talent arbitrage available in the power=
 space.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">No ambitious genius wants to work for th=
e utility. But the Anduril of Electricity? The company solving a never-endi=
ng series of interconnected hard problems to fix the trillion-dollar power =
market and usher in the electric future with other smart people? That&#8217=
;s the kind of problem smart people can&#8217;t resist.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Finding the really hard problem to solve with really smart people=
 has been Zach Dell&#8217;s quest.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">During colleg=
e, he recruited a team to go to India and build anaerobic digestion systems=
 to turn waste into compressed biogas that could be used to power stoves, l=
ights, and fans. Before senior year, he interned at Blackstone because as t=
he largest investment firm in the world, it seemed like the place to work w=
ith smart people and hunt for big problems. His first project proved that h=
unch right.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Blackstone was looking at buyi=
ng a lithium mine, which meant that it had to take a view on the price of l=
ithium, which meant that it had to take a view on battery demand. 70% of li=
thium goes to batteries. If you get your battery assumption right, you win.=
 If you get it wrong, you lose. As Zach did the research, he realized that =
a lot of people got it wrong: as with solar solar, </span><strong>experts k=
ept underestimating the exponential curve batteries were riding.</strong><s=
pan>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Hooked, Zach raised his hand to keep=
 working on energy projects, and as he did, the idea that there were going =
to be a ton of batteries coming online stuck with him.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">When he went to work at Thrive Capital after his first year at Black=
stone, he kept working on energy and hardware, kept researching batteries, =
and met with as many battery companies as he could. He wanted to understand=
 the best way to create and capture value from the battery wave he was conv=
inced was coming, and he didn&#8217;t see anyone doing it the way he would.=
&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Around the same time, Thrive made a large inves=
tment in Anduril, and Zach flew out to Costa Mesa, California to check out =
the factory. Naturally, Anduril&#8217;s Head of Manufacturing showed him ar=
ound.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-he=
