f Age of Miracles</a><span> covering is to build more nuclear. Nuclear is c=
lean, firm, baseload power. It&#8217;s predictable. We should absolutely, 1=
00% do that, and a host of startups are working to make it possible. But nu=
clear, as implemented in America at least, is slow to turn on and off. It c=
an&#8217;t respond to spikes in demand. It helps solve half the issue.&#160=
;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Another obvious solution is just to build mor=
e transmission and distribution. But if you&#8217;ve been reading Not Borin=
g, you know how incredibly difficult it is to build big things in America. =
Aside from nuclear, transmission might be the most difficult thing for us t=
