olor: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">running at a load of 48=
=2E8 GW</a><span>. That&#8217;s a load=20=
factor of 57%.&#160;&#160;</span></p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>Maximizing</em><span> load factor means the grid can o=
perate more efficiently. </span><em>Stabilizing</em><span> load factor help=
s to minimize fluctuations in demand, which can reduce strain on the grid a=
nd improve its overall reliability.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Batte=
ries can help maximize and stabilize load factor by charging when demand is=
 low, thereby increasing trough demand, and discharging when demand is high=
, thereby lowering peak demand.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-cont=
