torage portfolios is a good business no matter how you slice it, so good th=
at Casey Handmer used an exclamation point when he </span><a href=3D"https:=
//substack.com/redirect/9cf0c5ed-2e41-4abb-8997-b4b72b355979?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">wrote</a><span>: &#8220;Indeed=
, while new solar farms take 5-20 years to pay for themselves, battery plan=
ts are so lucrative they&#8217;re often profitable by year two &#8211; whic=
h is unheard of in the energy infrastructure space!&#8221;</span></p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;"><span>Broad Reach, which was founded in 2019, was </span><a hre=
f=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/0667fb9e-1012-44aa-8ae8-e9fac88a9750?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">acquired for $1 b=
illion in equity value</a><span> in 2023, at just four years old, and with =
only 350 MW of storage in operation (with another 880 MW under construction=
). Now that batteries are getting cheaper, renewables are getting more plen=
tiful, and demand for electricity is picking up, building a profitable port=
folio of batteries is easier than it&#8217;s ever been.&#160;</span></p><p =
style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But to build the </span><em>most profitable</em><span>=
 portfolio, and one that alleviates the grid&#8217;s challenges, Base belie=
ves that you need to do a whole lot of hard things, at once, in such a way =
that the whole system works in a way that no competitor can match.&#160;</s=
pan></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You need to manufacture batteries, and design a w=
hole Deployment Factory, optimized to lower the cost of the whole installat=
ion at scale.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You need to offer the batteries as=
 part of a larger REP offering, and offer them at install cost (taking on t=
he cost of the battery yourself) in order to increase adoption.&#160;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">You need to turn that adoption into a distributed network o=
f batteries that produces demand signals in real-time, and can charge and d=
ispatch on-demand in order to profitably trade power and offer ancillary se=
rvices to the grid.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">And you need to start in Tex=
as, the most isolated and volatile grid in America, in order to create, and=
 capture, the most value.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">To make it more clear,=
 let&#8217;s look at that ERCOT summer 2023 chart again.&#160;</p><div clas=
