size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Many of these companies=
 are over 100 years old, the result of decades of mergers and acquisitions.=
 They&#8217;re among the largest and least innovative companies in the worl=
d. We shouldn&#8217;t just accept that they&#8217;re the best we can do.&#1=
60;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The utilities seem untouchable, even though =
if you were starting fresh, you would never build a utility with the genera=
tion portfolio that they have. You wouldn&#8217;t build coal plants &#8211;=
 utilities are spending millions to decommission them &#8211; you </span><e=
m>might </em><span>build some natural gas plants, and you&#8217;d build a w=
hole lot more solar and nuclear, like they&#8217;re all scrambling to do no=
w.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The mega-bull case for Base is that it=
 can build a modern utility by starting on the demand side instead of the s=
upply side. Fix the grid&#8217;s big bottleneck, build a power company that=
 customers actually love, hack away on all of the challenges that pop up wi=
th tech, and eventually, vertically integrate into supply.&#160;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">We&#8217;re going to need a lot more clean energy, and someone i=
s going to have to build it. With enough customers and enough batteries, Ba=
se will know who needs that power, when and where. It can build solar farms=
 and nuclear plants, sell direct to its own customers, and cut out the midd=
leman, lowering prices. It can produce energy, store it, and discharge it a=
s needed. The supply and demand books are hedges for each other.&#160;</p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">Like a bank that lends customer deposits, Base would have =
a lower cost of capital on supply by owning demand.&#160;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">If they pull it off, that will be a hard-earned advantage and the basis=
 for a generational company.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Base is a pri=
me </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/32b5d92c-ce04-4285-ace8-=
570a71e77053?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Tec=
hno-Industrial</a><span>. It plans to capture a big chunk of a large incumb=
ent-dominated topline and pair it with software-like margins. What does a P=
G&amp;E or Southern Company with high free cash flow margins look like?&#16=
0;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But all of that is in the future. The =
strategy makes sense, the team is strong, and the mission is big. For now, =
it&#8217;s about executing, learning, and iterating.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">Do that enough, and you just might end up building The Modern Power Co=
mpany of the Electric Era, one that makes the world an objectively better p=
lace.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"ba=
ckground: #dde3e6; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;">=
